cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.CY, cs.SI 

This paper discusses a protocol for anonymous communication in LANs, which is relevant to computer security (cs.CR) and computer networks (cs.NI). The protocol builds on Dining Cryptographers networks (DC-nets) and solves several of their limitations, which is relevant to distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the detection of disruption (jamming) attacks, which is relevant to cyber-physical systems (cs.CY) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
